##Before the quarantine, they went to four cities, ate with over 80 people

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

The Village Committee stuck the word "Fu" as a seal on the door lock. Photo courtesy of the respondents

This article is about 3577 words long

Estimated reading time 9 minutes

By Xu Jingran

Editor Jin jin-ja

Qin Zheng and her sister spent New Year's Eve in an ambulance.

In the car, sitting opposite the medical staff wearing protective clothing, not an inch of skin exposed, Qin Zheng through goggles to see each other's eyes.

Qin Zheng is from Jiaxing, a family of six with five people living in Wuhan. Only she is a graduate student in Hunan. As in previous years, before the Spring Festival, Qin Zheng went to Wuhan for the winter vacation, then returned to Jiaxing with her family.

This year, the family split up. On January 13, Qin Zheng and her sister set off from Wuhan's Hankou Railway Station, passing through Nanjing and Suzhou, traveling all the way, eating and drinking, and arriving in Jiaxing by car and boat on January 16. My parents set up a good business and drove back from Wuhan with my grandparents.

At the beginning of 2020, the journey had a different meaning. On New Year's Eve, Guzheng's sister had a fever. The paramedics who arrived listened to the sisters'itinerary and were silent for a while. Qin Zheng was silent, she surmised, "the other side should be quietly calculating (if confirmed infection) need to quarantine how many people. ".

The lights of the ambulance blazed all the way to a new hospital for the treatment of pneumonia.

It's the first day of the year of the boxer rat.

1

A few hours ago, the zither sisters and their parents and grandparents were enjoying a Chinese New Year dinner and watching the Spring Festival gala at home. Thermometer is the day before Qin Zheng father from the health station, according to the human hair, the Qin Zheng family took 6.

Five minutes later, Qin Zheng's thermometer reading is "37 degrees Celsius" , the sister's reading is "more than 37 points" , the whole family's temperature are slightly higher. Sister also some cough, said "hand acid, leg acid" , feeling "and the symptoms of the number.

The family surmised that it must have been because they had drunk wine at dinner or had turned off the air conditioner and caught a cold. Mother told Qin Zheng and sister to sleep in separate rooms, and to find a mask for her sister to wear.

After 11 o'clock in the evening, grandma and GRANDPA had a rest first, mom and dad also went back to the house. Sister is still coughing, Qin Zheng sister before going to bed and took a temperature, sister "37.4 degrees Celsius" , Qin Zheng suddenly "panic" , wake up mom and dad, give sister test again, "37.5 degrees Celsius" . My mother had "lost her footing and her legs were weak" . Father to call the village head said, "Wuhan to a little fever. " The village contacted the ambulance.

Although Qin Zheng did not have a fever, the two sisters shared a room and board an ambulance in order to keep company with her 19-year-old sister. Before setting out, Qin Zheng brought along an eyebrow pencil, "because I do not know how long to live. ".

2

Eyebrow Pencil and did not come in Handy, in the hospital does not need to see people, Qin Zheng face has not washed.

On the first night at 1:30, after they arrived at the hospital, they had a CT scan and a throat swab nucleic acid test. The Qin Zheng Sisters were admitted to the negative pressure isolation ward. There were two doors in the ward, one for medical staff to pass through and the other connecting the corridor for patients to pass through. The nurse told the sisters not to leave the room as much as possible. "All the people living around were isolated patients whose test results had not come out. ". There were no curtains on the windows of the ward. Qin Zheng had seen people sleeping with masks on.

Sister soon fell asleep, but Qin Zheng could not sleep, brush until 6 o'clock in the morning.

Qin Zheng's first impression of the new crown pneumonia epidemic was on December 31,2019, when she brushed a "Wuhan unknown pneumonia, the Expert Group went to investigate" hot search, but also specifically screenshots posted in the family group, exhorting the family members in Wuhan not to run around, ask Your father who is away from home to "don't take the Hankou Railway Station road when returning to Wuhan" and wear a mask.

"after more than 10 days, also did not see more news" , Qin Zheng self-proclaimed "as if in evil general forgot the pneumonia this matter" , thought "the past" . Her plans for the trip with her sister were in no way affected.

Visit Relatives and friends, buy New Year goods, a family ready for the upcoming Spring Festival. On January 20, at noon on the 26th day of the 12th month, the Guzheng family hosted a dinner for guests. There were about 80 relatives and friends present at the dinner. During the dinner, some relatives joked, "I heard that you are from Wuhan and can not be near you. " Everyone raised their wine glasses and laughed. By the end of the meal, public media reports of the new pneumonia were still "not clear evidence of human-to-human transmission. ". That very night, Zhong Nanshan spoke out, affirming the idea of human-to-human transmission.

3

The family's home in Wuhan, about 7.5 kilometers from the south China Seafood Market, is a 15 minute drive away. Although the family has never been to the market, Qin is still upset. She remembers her experiences waiting for a bus at Hankou Railway Station and traveling by car, in public places people eat and talk, and the Hustle and bustle seems normal.

Even if the new coronavirus "human-to-human" phenomenon has been confirmed, a family of six, only two grandchildren attention. Guzheng's parents are also planning to attend the wedding of their friend's son on the sixth day of the Lunar New Year. Qin estimates that there will be more than 30 Wuhan returnees at the reception. "Many of us here work in Wuhan. ". She turned on the television in the hope that the news would convince the elderly, but most of the news was not about pneumonia.

Until January 22, Qin Zheng parents learned from acquaintances, "there is a village catering, during a Wuhan homecoming fever, 7 table guests were all isolated. ". They began to be genuinely alarmed. Then came the news that a friend in Wenzhou had been diagnosed. "It felt like it was right around the corner. ".

"My sister and I have been doing a lot of micro-blogging, and we thought, if something happens to us, we'll go to Nanjing, and we'll all be ruined... " Guzheng's parents wrote down the names of nearly a hundred contacts. Guzheng, who has seen the progress of a diagnostician on television, is sure to be criticised, but she is adamant that "if I had known it was this serious, I would never have gone out to party, let alone travel" .

Fortunately, the sisters did not abnormal CT examination, body temperature since the day of admission to normal, two viral nucleic acid tests were negative, follow-up without other clinical symptoms. Guzheng's parents had also been to the hospital for a CT scan and nucleic acid tests, both of which were normal. Qin Zheng had a family dinner with the relatives and friends of the body is not abnormal.

On the third day of the Lunar New Year, the hospital told the Qin Zheng Sisters to leave the hospital. When they were admitted to the hospital for quarantine, all of the town's Wuhan returnees had been quarantined to the hotel. Qin Zheng Mother has sent her daughter a small video, men and women, old and young carrying luggage, wearing a mask, check-in. The village sent a car to take the two sisters to the quarantined hotel, which had been requisitioned by the town.

"A look to know that the car is to pick you up, " Qin Zheng recalled, the driver only two eyes exposed, although wearing is not the kind of medical staff protective clothing, but the whole body is wrapped up. They talked on the phone and text before they got on the bus, and they haven't spoken since. The car traveled nearly 20 kilometers, the window is always down, cold wind purr into the car.

4

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, while the Qin Zheng Sisters were waiting for the results of their first nucleic acid test, they saw "they have been diagnosed" on their family wechat group.

The news was released by Qin Zheng's uncle, who said "two cases have been confirmed in our village" . The uncle got the news from the Group of friends, and the "gossip" , whose source was almost untraceable, was turned into the family group.

The whole family knows that "there are two cases in the village" refers to the Qin Zheng Sisters. Only they are the people in the village who are currently being sent to the hospital. Before that, Qin Zheng had also reported his own situation in the family group and told his relatives not to move around, but she had no idea that the path to debunking a rumor started by debunking it herself, "feeling like people are imagining the results of our tests. ".

In the group of villagers, some people posted, "in the morning, I saw a car with Hubei license plate a driving toward the village. " Some people posted, "don't let them come in. " Some people posted, "hurry up and grab it. " Qin Zheng replied, "if you see it, report it to the village and ask the village to verify it. ". She feels a bit cruel, "everybody is a village, just a few people work in Wuhan" .

Some in the crowd posted roadblock maps saying "the Jiaxing road is closed, " while Qin Zheng sought official news to dispel rumors. Some in the crowd said that "hotels have been requisitioned, " and she went back to the real situation. Others said that "the epidemic is more serious than you think. " She responded to the actual quarantine. Qin Zheng understood the villagers'speculative behavior, exactly how many people are in isolation, who is in isolation, isolation period how long, they do not know. Qin Zheng Thought: "If the village can timely report the situation to those who have not been quarantined will be a little better? "

Early in the morning of the New Year's Day, Qin Zheng's grandmother went out and met a villager. The villager saw an ambulance the night before and asked the old man if he knew who had taken the family.

Because she went to bed early, grandma didn't know she was taking her granddaughter.

5

On January 31, the Qin Zheng family returned home after a 14-day isolation period ended on the day of their return from Wuhan. Dad Put a lock on the yard door and stressed to grandma and GRANDPA "no going out to play" .

On sunny days, grandma and GRANDPA sit in the yard in the Sun.

Neighbors shouting through the gate fence, some people know the Qin Zheng a weekday outside work, the family did not store food, to send them from home to grow vegetables. Grandma asked the neighbors to leave the dishes by the door and pick them up later. The neighbor asked, "is it so exaggerated? " This time the old man explained it to them. A passer-by shouted at the House, "do you want to play Mahjong? " The old man said, "don't play, don't gather, don't wander off. ".

But the end of the 14-day quarantine period did not signal the end of the crisis. One of the Qinzheng family's former quarantined hotels was diagnosed with new pneumonia after a 14-day quarantine period. The study by Zhong Nanshan's team also said the incubation period of the virus could be up to 24 days.

The village where the Qin Zheng is located is "closed" , the path is set up at checkpoints, only registered residents can enter here, in and out of the villagers have to measure the temperature. February 2, Qin Zheng home was also "closed" , but the village is very gentle, stick to the door lock is a "blessing" word. If you have any material needs at home, report to the village committee and the village will send it to you. Village Committees dragged speakers around the village every day to publicize the prevention and control of the epidemic. Qin Zheng heard that he and his sister on the ambulance that night, the village committee was "her sudden situation" pulled out of bed from the meeting.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A pink notice posted by the village committee outside the fence at the home of Qin Zheng

On February 11, the village removed the "seal" from the home of Qin Zheng. The family, who ended a 10-day extended isolation period, has agreed that "home is the safest place" and is continuing the isolation at home. In a way, Guzheng felt lucky to have a "home" to live in. One of her friends was quarantined in a hotel after recovering from hospital in Wenzhou, but because she had lived in Wuhan for years and did not have a home in Wenzhou, "she was going to be homeless at the end of the quarantined period, and her relatives' neighbors in the residential area objected to their living there. ".

The sisters haven't started school yet, and the family is spending the Lantern Festival in Jiaxing. In Wuhan to do offline clothing business, "their own to pay their own wages" Qin Zheng parents are ready for the first half of the year will not return to Wuhan. Although the business is completely shut down, but the shop rent or pay, they are glad "did not hire" , "or life is important, money, forget it" . Some of guzheng's parents'clients have been diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia.

One late night, Qin Zheng sent a message with 6 pictures of friends circle, all of Wuhan's food. She missed the city, did not know when the epidemic can really be lifted, people can breathe freely, move freely, looking up at the sky.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A screenshot of Qin Zheng's friendagenda post

Through the gate fence, can only see the bare field Qin Zheng really look tired, but she knows, where the Lotus root, wait until the summer will grow into a patch of Lotus.

(at the request of the interviewee, Qin Zheng is a pseudonym. Ma Kui contributed research
